CREATING DATE TABLE AND CALCULATED COLUMN 9

STEP 1- Go to Data view then Click create table

STEP 2- Copy and paste this DAX(Date Table = CALENDARAUTO() )then enter

STEP 3- Select the Date table change the date format

STEP 4- go to model view and create one to many relationship

Follow the GIF below to apply the above steps  

Next you can copy paste the DAX for formula I listed below or you can download it as a word document by clicking the above icon

1.    Total Sale = SUM(sales[Total Revnue ])

2.    Total Profit = SUM(sales [Net Profit ])

3.    Gross Profit Margin % = DIVIDE([Total profit],[Total Sales],0)

4.    LY Profit Margin = CALCULATE([Gross Profit Margin %],SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR('Date Table'[Date]))

5.     YOY% = [Gross Profit Margin %]-[LY Profit Margin]

6.    YOY% kpi = SWITCH(TRUE(), [YOY%]<0,UNICHAR(9660),UNICHAR(9650))&ROUND([YOY%],4)*100 & "%"

7.    KPI Arrow = IF([YOY%]>=0, "green","Red")

you repeat this steps to create Measures for the rest of DAXs I listed above
